{
  "texts": [
    "The KVN 129 GHz data suffer from larger uncertainties due to a stronger influence from weather.",
    "We fit a power-law model to the total flux densities (i.e., F tot ∝ ν +α tot).",
    "We find α tot ≈ -0.17 when 129 GHz data are included, while α tot ≈ -0.11 when they are excluded.",
    "By extrapolating a power-law model with a range α tot ≈ -(0.11 -0.17) to 230 GHz, we estimate F tot,230 = 0.72 -0.80 Jy.",
    "While this range of values is lower than the ALMA interferometric measurements during the EHT observations (∼1.11-1.18 Jy; Table 3 in Goddi et al. 2021), it only includes the total flux density within the inner 500 × 500 µas 2, which is nearly three orders of magnitude below the resolution limit of ALMA."
  ]
}